messages.msgSnippet: Thank you everyone :-) ... Whaaaat?!? Just because I may have lead some to believe I m a little empathically challenged in the instinct department where
messages.messageBody:
Thank you everyone :-)

on 1/31/02 1:40 PM, SandraDodd@... at SandraDodd@... wrote:

> She shouldn't be a La Leche League leader, I think

Whaaaat?!? Just because I may have lead some to believe I'm a little
empathically challenged in the instinct department where infants are
concerned? You're suggesting that might be a handicap in relating?

> but she should be the Queen of Unschoolers.

While we recognize what a great honor this is, we will most respectfully
decline. We much prefer being a gently spoken, if long winded at times,
member of the masses than a leader or role model. We feel our integrity
benefits from the necessity of constantly testing it, rather than resting
upon our pointy crowns.

And, besides, I'm not sure a goddess and a queen can coexist peacefully in
the same forum. Especially if the goddess is certain the queen will, when
necessity dictates, clean up behind her. ;-)

(And you people are writing way too much! I'll never find out what happened
on Monday at this rate!)

Joyce

Me too.
Her stuff is the coolest.

She shouldn't be a La Leche League leader, I think, but she should be the
Queen of Unschoolers.

Sometimes, too, I have gone off like Donald Duck about something and while
I'm off recovering, watching Black Adder or something, I know that Joyce will
come along like a peace-loving Mickey Mouse and paraphrase my rant, or
dissolve it with a sweeter, better answer.

Sandra
